I have never ordered something so large without touching or sitting in it first but we took a chance and these exceeded my expectations. I read all of the reviews and some things stood out to me negatively that I wanted to address. Some say the fabric is scratchy. Its not. Its not a velvet or chenille so it isnt soft to the touchy but its definitely not scratchy. Its quite smooth to the touch. It feels like a good quality sturdy fabric. The length of this couch is substantial. Its a great sleeping couch! I can lay down full length. I am 5 7 with room to spare. Another issue I was preparing for was the color. I wasnt sure if it was a yelloworange beige based on some of the pictures I saw. The color is a true creambeige neutral and has soft light brown tones. It is absolutely beautiful! Another issue I was prepared for were the legs. I was actually planning on painting them as soon as I got them, which would be easy to do but I actually think they are fine and I like them as is. They arent as scary red as some of the other reviews photos suggest. I did give it a good coat of Scotchgard since I have four children as it is susceptible to stains because of the light color but Im not worried! Definitely a winner!. Ann.
